From d97037907297614a7e5e117dcc7c41ed11df6db7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bartosz Golaszewski <bartosz.golaszewski@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 14:49:59 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 07/22] tools: fix an integer overflow bug in parse_period()

If p * m exceeds ULLONG_MAX, the result wraps modulo 2^64. The wrapped
value may be less than LLONG_MAX, passing the guard and returning
a completely wrong period value. Check the overflow before the
multiplication.

Fixes: 8ffb6489286f ("tools: line name focussed rework")
Reported-by: 4fqr <4fqr@proton.me>
Tested-by: Vincent Fazio <vfazio@xes-inc.com>
Reviewed-by: Vincent Fazio <vfazio@xes-inc.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260407-treewide-fixes-v1-8-66c9744a56a3@oss.qualcomm.com
Signed-off-by: Bartosz Golaszewski <bartosz.golaszewski@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 tools/tools-common.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/tools-common.c b/tools/tools-common.c
index 4e6bb3d..82f7b88 100644
--- a/tools/tools-common.c
+++ b/tools/tools-common.c
@@ -150,9 +150,9 @@ long long parse_period(const char *option)
 		m = 1000;
 	}
 
-	p *= m;
-	if (*end != '\0' || p > LLONG_MAX)
+	if (m != 0 && p > ULLONG_MAX / m)
 		return -1;
+	p *= m;
 
 	return p;
 }
